"Bit of a bugger."

219
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:12,558
DON: You inhale the polio virus
from droplets in the air.

220
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:14,631
The same way
you catch a cold.

221
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,113
It passes into
the blood stream,

222
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:20,319
into the central
nervous system,

223
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:24,712
and attacks a big group of
cells in the spinal cord.

224
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,230
The result is
you become like a rag doll.

225
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,630
You can't move anything
from the neck down.

226
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,910
Can't even breathe
for yourself.

227
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:44,678
Right, and, um, how long
will he be like this?

228
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,236
The paralysis
is irreversible.

229
00:16:57,840 --> 00:17:01,037
A good respiration system will
maintain life for a while.

230
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,838
We're talking
a matter of months.

231
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:17,914
(RESPIRATOR HISSING)

232
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:44,551
Tell me what we can do.

233
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,791
Do you want to go home?

234
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:56,551
After the baby's born.

235
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,118
